  "What is the trace of a matrix in relation to its characteristic polynomial?": "",
  "The trace has no relationship to the characteristic polynomial": "",
  "The trace equals the constant term of the characteristic polynomial": "",
  "The trace equals the sum of the roots of the characteristic polynomial": "",
  "The trace equals the leading coefficient of the characteristic polynomial": "",
  "The trace of a matrix equals the sum of its eigenvalues, which are the roots of the characteristic polynomial. For an n x n matrix, the coefficient of lambda^(n-1) equals (-1) times the trace.": "",
  "What does the Cayley-Hamilton theorem state?": "",
  "Every matrix has at least one real eigenvalue": "",
