  "Similar matrices have different characteristic polynomials": "",
  "Every matrix satisfies its own characteristic polynomial": "",
  "The Cayley-Hamilton theorem states that every square matrix satisfies its own characteristic equation. If p(lambda) is the characteristic polynomial of A, then p(A) = 0 (the zero matrix).": "",
  "What is a 'monic polynomial' in the context of characteristic polynomials?": "",
  "A polynomial whose highest-degree term has coefficient 1": "",
