  "det(A - lambda I) = (0-lambda)(-5-lambda) - (1)(-6) = lambda^2 + 5lambda + 6 = (lambda + 2)(lambda + 3). The eigenvalues are -2 and -3, both negative, so the system is stable.": "",
  "A data scientist computes the covariance matrix C = [[4, 2], [2, 3]] for a dataset. What is the product of the eigenvalues of C?": "",
